frameDefinitions: An Item is in a state of dryness.
A particular piece of Information is evaluated for its accuracy.
A Speaker communicates about a Topic in such a way as to mislead an Addressee, either by telling outright lies or by presenting a message in a misleading form.
One phenomenon, the Predictive_phenomenon is an indication of the future or current (but still uncertain) existence of another phenomenon, the Future_phenomenon.
A Cognizer makes a judgment about an Evaluee.
A Manipulator gets his Victim to perform a Resulting_action against what their better judgment would have been at the time.
frameExamples: Is your reputation at risk due to <t>incorrect</t> information?
I <t>lied</t> to you about your Christmas present.
JUDGMENT:  She <t>admired</t> Einstein for his character.
Are you trying to tell me that Ace <t>blackmailed</t> you into becoming his lover?
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Item</fen> exists in a state of dryness.
The <fen>Information</fen> matches or does not match the facts of the world.
The <fen>Source</fen> is the agent who holds the correct/incorrect information.
The event which communicates the <fen>Information</fen>.
The Topic about which the Source has accurate information.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Information</fen> or the <fen>Source</fen> is correct.
The person who uses language in the written or spoken modality to convey a deceptive Message to the Addressee.
The person that receives a Message from the Speaker.
<fen>Topic</fen> is the entity to which the proposition or propositions  relate, that they are about.
The time at which the deception occurs.
The location at which the deception occurs.
<fen>Predictive_phenomenon</fen> provides evidence for the existence or the nature of the <fen>Outcome</fen> of <fen>Future_phenomenon</fen>.
<fen>Future_phenomenon</fen> is that phenomenon that is predicted to occur or have a particular quality.
The role <fen>Outcome</fen> identifies those expressions that indicate how the <fen>Future_phenomenon</fen> is expected to turn out based on the evidence of the <fen>Predictive_phenomenon</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the omen is occuring.
The location where something good or bad might occur.
The <fen>Cognizer</fen> makes the judgment. This role is typically expressed as the External Argument (or in a <ment>by</ment>-PP in passives).
Evaluee is the person or thing about whom/which a judgment is made. With verbs this role is typically expressed as Object:
Typically, there is a constituent expressing the <t>Reason</t> for the Judge's judgment. It is usually a <ment>for</ment>-PP, e.g.
<fen>Expressor</fen> is the body part or action by a body part that conveys the judgment made by the <fen>Cognizer</fen>.
The person who gets the Victim to act against their interest.
The person who the Manipulator gets to do something they would not have done had no pressure or deception been applied.
What the <fen>Manipulator</fen> intends to make the <fen>Victim</fen> do and the <fen>Victim</fen> actually does.
The role goods is anything (including labor, time, or legal rights) that can be taken away.
The time when the manipulation occurs.
The location where the <fen>Manipulator</fen> manipulates the <fen>Victim</fen>.
listRoleExamples: <fex>Politicians</fex> do nothing but tell lies about money.
You deceived me <fex>about the location of the diamonds</fex>.
<fex>To achieve so much this year</fex> augurs well for the future.
This move presages <fex>a freeze on the granting of new concessions</fex>.
It all bodes <fex>well</fex> for the future.
The storm bodes ill for you <fex>here</fex> .
<fex>The boss</fex> appreciates you for your diligence.
The boss appreciates <fex>you</fex> for your diligence.
She viewed him with an appreciative <fex>gaze</fex>.
Leslie blackmailed <fex>the watch</fex> out of John.
